quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  10,7,"Verily, those who expect not for the meeting with Us, and are content with the life of this world, and are comforted (or secure) therein, and those who are neglectful of our Signs (or revelations)"
  10,8,Their resort is the Fire because of that which they have earned
  10,9,"Verily, those who believe and act righteously, their Lord guides them by their faith; beneath them shall rivers flow in the Gardens of Delight"
  10,10,"Their cry therein shall be, \"Glory be to Thee, O Allah!\" and their salutation therein shall be, \"Peace!\" and the end of their cry shall be, \"Praise be to Allah, the Lord (Cherisher and Sustainer) of the Worlds"
  10,11,"And if Allah should hasten for men the evil they earn, as they would fain hasten on the good, their respite would surely have expired. But We suffer those who look not for (or expect not) the meeting with Us to wander blindly on in their rebellion"
  10,12,"When misfortune touches man, he calls Us, whether reclining, sitting or standing; but when We have removed from him his distress, he passes on as though he had not called on Us because of the misfortune that touched him. Thus unto the extravagant is made"
  10,13,"We have already destroyed generations before you when they did wrong, and there came to them their Messengers with manifest signs, but they would not believe. Thus do We reward the guilty people"
  10,14,"Then We made you Vicegerents (or their successors) in the earth after them, that We may see how you will act"